## 3. Technology Stack

### Backend
- Python 3.10+, FastAPI, Uvicorn
- PyTorch (CPU or CUDA) — for loading `dino_v3_linear.pth`
- Pillow — image decoding and preprocessing
- pytest — testing

### Browser Extension
- Manifest V3
- TypeScript → compiled JS (Vite or Webpack — pick one, document it)
- Vanilla JS/TS in content script (no React, no heavy frameworks — keep it lightweight)
- HTML + CSS + vanilla JS for popup and options pages
- Jest — unit testing

### Android App
- Flutter (Dart) — single codebase targeting Android only
- `flutter_inappwebview` — WebView with JavaScript channel support
- Kotlin via platform channel — for `MediaProjection`, `WindowManager`, foreground service
- `shared_preferences` — settings storage
- `http` package — sending frames to FastAPI backend

---

## 4. System Architecture

### 4.1 Data Flow (Extension)

```
[Any Web Page]
     │
     ▼
[Content Script]
  • Finds <video> elements via MutationObserver
  • Draws frame to offscreen <canvas> every 500ms
  • canvas.toBlob(jpeg) → sends blob to service worker
  • Immediately frees canvas memory
     │
     ▼  chrome.runtime.sendMessage
[Service Worker (MV3)]
  • Receives blob
  • Applies BR-01 threshold
  • POSTs to http://localhost:8000/analyze-image
     │
     ▼  JSON response
[Service Worker]
  • If detected=true → sendMessage back to content script: { action: 'BLUR' }
  • If detected=false → sendMessage: { action: 'CLEAR' }
     │
     ▼  chrome.tabs.sendMessage
[Content Script]
  • BLUR  → videoElement.style.filter = 'blur(24px)'
  • CLEAR → videoElement.style.filter = ''
```

**Rule: The content script NEVER calls the backend directly. All AI calls go through the service worker.**

### 4.2 Data Flow (Android — In-App Browser)

```
[Flutter WebView]
  • JS bridge injected on page load
  • JS captures video frame to canvas → toDataURL(jpeg) → postMessage to Flutter
     │
     ▼  JavaScriptChannel callback
[Flutter Dart Layer]
  • Decodes base64 frame
  • HTTP POST to http://<configured-ip>:8000/analyze-image
     │
     ▼  JSON response
[Flutter Dart Layer]
  • detected=true  → setState: show BackdropFilter overlay over WebView
  • detected=false → setState: hide overlay
```

### 4.3 Data Flow (Android — Screen Capture Overlay)

```
[Kotlin Foreground Service]
  • MediaProjection captures screen bitmap every 500ms
  • Compresses to JPEG bytes
  • Sends bytes to Flutter via MethodChannel (or calls backend directly from Kotlin)
     │
     ▼
[FastAPI Backend]
  • Runs inference on frame
  • Returns { detected, confidence, action }
     │
     ▼
[Kotlin Service]
  • detected=true  → WindowManager adds full-screen overlay View
  • detected=false → WindowManager removes overlay View
  • Overlay is always rendered above all other apps (TYPE_APPLICATION_OVERLAY)
```

### 4.4 Business Rules (enforce exactly as written)

| Rule ID | Rule | Where Enforced |
|---|---|---|
| BR-01 | Confidence threshold floor = 75% regardless of user sensitivity setting: `effective = max(0.75, userSensitivity)` | Backend `inference.py` AND service worker |
| BR-02 | All frame data purged within 500ms of analysis — never written to disk | Content script (canvas reset), Kotlin service (bitmap.recycle()), backend (del tensor) |
| BR-03 | Profanity blacklist is a static editable list; changes require no app restart | Extension options page / Android settings screen |
| BR-04 | User settings always override defaults | `chrome.storage.local` / `SharedPreferences` read before every inference cycle |
| BR-05 | Audio mute duration = exactly 1500 ms | `setTimeout` (extension) / `Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 1500))` (Flutter) |
| BR-06 | TMDb stub respects 3 req/min rate limit with a token bucket (ready to activate) | Backend `metadata.py` stub |
| BR-07 | Blur/overlay layer must always render above video content | CSS `filter` on video element; `TYPE_APPLICATION_OVERLAY` for Android WindowManager |
| BR-08 | Any PIN/password gate on settings: min 8 characters including 1 digit | Options page / Android settings if implemented |

