## 9. Android Implementation Details

### AndroidManifest.xml — Required Permissions
```xml
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_MEDIA_PROJECTION" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS" />

<service
    android:name=".OverlayService"
    android:foregroundServiceType="mediaProjection"
    android:exported="false" />
```

### OverlayService.kt — Key Implementation Rules
- Start as a foreground service with an ongoing notification immediately on `onCreate()`.
- Use `ImageReader` + `VirtualDisplay` from MediaProjection to receive frames.
- On each frame: compress to JPEG (quality 70), send to backend, call `image.close()` immediately.
- Add/remove overlay via `WindowManager` with `LayoutParams.TYPE_APPLICATION_OVERLAY`.
- The overlay view must have `LayoutParams.FLAG_NOT_TOUCHABLE or LayoutParams.FLAG_NOT_FOCUSABLE` so the user can still interact with the underlying app.
- Stop the service cleanly on notification action "Stop Protection" — release `VirtualDisplay`, `ImageReader`, `MediaProjection`.

### Flutter ↔ Kotlin Communication
- Use a single `MethodChannel` named `"com.safeview/overlay"`.
- Flutter calls: `startCapture(sensitivity, categories)`, `stopCapture()`
- Kotlin calls back to Flutter via `EventChannel` named `"com.safeview/status"` to stream detection events and service status updates.

### In-App Browser (Flutter)
- Use `flutter_inappwebview` package.
- On `onLoadStop`: inject a JavaScript snippet that:
  1. Finds all `<video>` elements
  2. Sets up a `requestAnimationFrame` loop gated at 500 ms
  3. Draws each video frame to an offscreen canvas
  4. Calls `canvas.toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.7)`
  5. Posts the base64 string to Flutter via `JavaScriptChannel` named `"SafeViewBridge"`
- Flutter receives the base64 string, decodes it, POSTs to backend, and on detection sets overlay state.
- The overlay is a `Stack` with the `InAppWebView` underneath and a `BackdropFilter(filter: ImageFilter.blur(sigmaX: 24, sigmaY: 24))` on top, toggled by a state boolean.

