## 10. UI/UX Requirements

### Brand
- Primary background: `#0D1B2A` (deep navy)
- Accent: `#00B4D8` (teal)
- Text: `#FFFFFF`
- Warning/offline: `#FF6B6B` (red)
- Active indicator: `#2ECC71` (green), pulsing animation
- Font: IBM Plex Sans (bundle locally — no Google Fonts CDN call at runtime)

### Extension Popup
- Protection ON/OFF toggle (persists to `chrome.storage.local`)
- Status dot: green (monitoring) / red (backend offline) / grey (idle)
- Count of active filters
- "Open Settings" link
- No raw confidence numbers shown to user

### Extension Options
- Per-category toggles: Nudity, Violence, Kissing, Profanity, LGBTQ+ Themes
- Sensitivity slider with three labelled stops: Low (0.60) / Medium (0.75) / High (0.90)
- Backend URL input + "Test Connection" button
- Profanity word list: add/remove entries, saved immediately on change
- "Reset to defaults" button

### Android Dashboard
- Two-mode toggle: "Browser Mode" vs "Screen Overlay Mode"
- Protection ON/OFF for each mode
- Live status feed (scrolling log of AI detections — category and timestamp only, no pixel data)
- Link to Settings

### Android Settings
- Same category toggles and sensitivity slider as extension
- Backend IP/URL field (default: `http://10.0.2.2:8000` for emulator, `http://192.168.x.x:8000` for real device)
- "Test Connection" button
- Permissions status section: shows which permissions are granted/missing with deep-link buttons to OS settings

